 and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellenor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor  , the result of blending with   Ellen ."]},{"name":"Elenor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]},{"name":"Elinor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Eleanor Sellinge Of England was born on 1 July 1347, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Thomas Sellinge. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1 July 1347–":"1. juuli 1347–Surnud","1341–Male":"1341–Surnud","1362–1465":"1362–1465","1347–Female":"1347–Surnud","1347":"1347","1 July 1347":"1. juuli 1347","1465":"1465","1341":"1341","1362":"1362","Hythe, Kent, England":"Hythe, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1 July 1347–":"1. heinäkuuta 1347–Kuollut","1341–Male":"1341–Kuollut","1362–1465":"1362–1465","1347–Female":"1347–Kuollut","1347":"1347","1 July 1347":"1. heinäkuuta 1347","1465":"1465","1341":"1341","1362":"1362","Hythe, Kent, England":"Hythe, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1 July 1347–":"1 juillet 1347–Décédée","1341–Male":"1341–Décédé","1362–1465":"1362–1465","1347–Female":"1347–Décédée","1347":"1347","1 July 1347":"1 juillet 1347","1465":"1465","1341":"1341","1362":"1362","Hythe, Kent, England":"Hythe, Kent, Angleterre, Royaum